race.description: Half Yours Caulfield Cup Winner Handicap
race.comment: KIRKLISTON BLU (4) has built steadily into his campaign and looks ready to peak fourth-up. With plenty of miles in the legs, the trip holds no concerns and he should give himself every chance again up on speed. Hard to beat. RICH CHAMPAGNE (1) was too bad to be true last start but has since been back to the trials to reset. His prior form reads strongly and from the low draw Opperman should give him a peach. Very competitive. CAPULET (5) hasn't broken through for some time but her best efforts measure up. The wide alley makes things tricky, yet she still rates among the hopes. MAGNETIC EDGE (6) lacks early speed but will relish a genuine tempo. Expect him to be charging late. EVENTUALLY (2) was a barnstorming winner last time and deserves respect again.
